Create new file: touch <file1> <file2> ... <filen>
Create new file and write text on it: cat > <filename>
						  Display it: cat filename
Copy from one filename to another: cp text newtext
Combine two txt files into one: cat file1 fil2 > file_merged
Delete a text file: rm file

Change permission of file newtext: chmod  newtext
chmod : 7 - Owner	7 - Group	7 - Others
		Each 7 is broken into 3 parts: r - 4	w - 2	x - 1
		chmod 777 <filename>
		rwxrwxrwx <filename>
Rename the newtext to oldtext: mv newtext oldtext
Create new directory: mkdir <my_dir>
Move the files oldtext and matter to the directory mydir: mv -t mydir oldtext matter
														  tree -r
Display current date: date + "	%d/	%m/	%y"
Count the number of users current logged into system: who -q
